FBIS3-55220 "drsov004_b_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Passes Decree on Counterintelligence Service LD0501174194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1348 GMT 5 Jan 94 LD0501174194 Moscow INTERFAX Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin has passed the decree confirming the provision on the Federal Counter-Intelligence Service and its structure, well-informed sources told Interfax. This service's director Nikolay Golushko and his first deputy Sergey Stepashin, are working out the selection criteria for the personnel of the former Security Ministry, disbanded by Boris Yeltsin last December.
